Does she love me? I have left 
you. That is how you 
will know you are my 
baby Tom, I am 
sitting on my dirt 
bike on the deck. Will you 
come out from the kitchen 
and watch the people with me? Yes, 
and we were strong-limbed 
and browning, and back. 
I went down and down. 
I didn’t know how to 
save the world. Now, I don’t 
know how to talk to 
her, my mother didn’t 
know how to end this 
poem. On “Torment” I 
wrote: “You may want 
to find a line of 
tenderness to walk 
tonight. But wishing 
for something— a 
deer, a possum, a 
squirrel, anything— 
